BBVA, Belgacom, Shell, UBS, Unilever: European Equity Preview

-- B y   V i c t o r i a   T a y l o r
-- 
2011-08-15T01:56:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-15/bbva-belgacom-shell-ubs-unilever-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in European trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The Stoxx  Europe  600 Index rose 3.7 percent to 237.49. The
Stoxx 50 Index gained 3.8 percent to 2,248.38. The Euro Stoxx 50
Index, a benchmark measure for nations using the euro, increased
4.2 percent to 2,307.33.  Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA (BBVA)  :  Spain ’s
second-largest lender hired banker Gabriel Bochi from Bank of
America Corp. as part of an effort to strengthen its Latin
America bond underwriting business, according to people familiar
with the matter. The shares added 6.2 percent to 6.43 euros.  Belgacom SA (BELG)  : The largest telephone company in
 Belgium  faces an antitrust probe of its planned purchase of The
Phone House retail stores, Belgium’s Competition Council said in
an e-mailed statement. Belgacom rose 2.9 percent to 23.11 euros.  EON AG (EOAN GY): Chief Executive Officer Johannes Teyssen
said the German utility is open to discussions about cooperation
in areas such as the construction of new  power plants ,  Der
Spiegel  said. Direct “participation” by OAO Gazprom would make
“little sense” for EON, Teyssen said. The shares surged 4.8
percent to 14.81 euros.  Grupo Empresarial Ence SA (ENC)  : The Spanish pulp
producer should be valued at 1.5 billion euros ($2.1 billion) by
the stock market, more than double current levels, Expansion
said, citing Chief Executive Officer Ignacio de Colmenares. The
shares added 4.6 percent to 2.30 euros.  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  : Europe’s largest bank by
market value is in talks to sell Cambridge Water Plc for about
100 million pounds ($163 million), the Sunday Times reported,
without saying where it got the information. The shares rose 3
percent to 551.8 pence.  Kardex AG (KARN)  : Adriano Agosti, who has been building
his stake in the Swiss provider of static-storage systems, wants
the company to scrap plans for a capital increase and instead
merge with  Swisslog Holding AG (SLOG)  , Finanz und Wirtschaft
said, citing a letter to the board. Kardex shares jumped 9.9
percent to 16.7 francs.  Munich Re  (MUV2 GY): The world’s biggest reinsurer has
almost halved its holdings in stocks in recent weeks because of
the debt crisis,  Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung  said, citing an
interview with Chief Financial Officer Joerg Schneider. The
shares climbed 3.5 percent to 92.14 euros.  Royal Dutch Shell Plc (RDSA)  : Europe’s biggest oil
company said an oil leak from its Gannet Alpha platform in the
 North Sea  “is under control.” Shell rose 3.5 percent to 22.93
euros.  Schroders Plc (SDR)  : The U.K.’s largest independent
money manager is set to take over the running of the 370
million-pound ($602 million) Invista Property Foundation Trust,
the  Sunday Times reported , without saying where it got the
information. The stock rose 0.6 percent to 1,484 pence.  UBS AG (UBSN)  : The implementation of the Swiss-German
tax treaty may cost Swiss lenders about 500 million francs ($648
million), Patrick Odier, head of the Swiss Banking Association,
told SonntagsZeitung in an interview. UBS shares rose 5.7
percent to 11.67 francs.  Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN)   shares
advanced 4.4 percent to 23.6 francs.  Unilever (UNA NA): There’s no guarantee the world’s second-
largest consumer-goods company will match each year the 7
percent growth pace reported in the first half of 2011, NRC
Handelsblad said, citing an interview with Chief Executive
Officer Paul Polman. The company aims to double sales to about
80 billion euros “eventually,” he said. Unilever gained 2.8
percent to 22.53 euros.  Zurich Financial Services AG (ZURN)  :  Switzerland ’s
largest insurer will retain its Italian and Spanish bond
holdings, Finanz und Wirtschaft said, citing an interview with
Chief Executive Officer Martin Senn. The shares advanced 7.1
percent to 171.5 francs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Victoria Taylor in New York at 
